# Theme And Styling

- Prefer theme tokens from `src/theme` and canonical theme utilities over hardcoded values.
- Avoid introducing new inline style objects in non-trivial UI; extract styles into `*.styles.ts`.
- Do not add new duplicate theme entrypoints; reuse existing canonical imports.
- Keep spacing, typography, and colors semantic (token names), not raw literals.
- Preserve dark/light support when editing visual components.
- For quick one-off layout wrappers, inline styles are acceptable only when minimal and obvious.
